#. <section class="sutta" id="mn19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn19:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 19"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 19"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn19:0.2"
msgid "Dvedhāvitakkasutta"
msgstr "Two Kinds of Thought"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn19:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn19:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn19:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn19:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn19:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on "
"awakening—I thought:"

msgctxt "mn19:2.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ dvidhā katvā dvidhā katvā vitakke vihareyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Why don’t I meditate by continually dividing my thoughts into two classes?’"

msgctxt "mn19:2.3"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yo cāyaṃ kāmavitakko yo ca byāpādavitakko yo ca "
"vihiṃsāvitakko—"
msgstr "So I assigned sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts"

msgctxt "mn19:2.4"
msgid "imaṃ ekaṃ bhāgamakāsiṃ;"
msgstr "to one class."

msgctxt "mn19:2.5"
msgid "yo cāyaṃ nekkhammavitakko yo ca abyāpādavitakko yo ca avihiṃsāvitakko—"
msgstr "And I assigned thoughts of renunciation, love, and kindness"

msgctxt "mn19:2.6"
msgid "imaṃ dutiyaṃ bhāgamakāsiṃ."
msgstr "to the second class."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.115"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato "
"uppajjati kāmavitakko."
msgstr ""
"Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a sensual thought arose."

msgctxt "mn19:3.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāmi:"
msgstr "I understood:"

msgctxt "mn19:3.3"
msgid "‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ kāmavitakko."
msgstr "‘This sensual thought has arisen in me."

msgctxt "mn19:3.4"
msgid ""
"So ca kho attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, "
"ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko "
"anibbānasaṃvattaniko’."
msgstr ""
"It leads to hurting myself, hurting others, and hurting both. It blocks "
"wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it doesn’t lead to extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn19:3.5"
msgid ""
"‘Attabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchati;"
msgstr "When I reflected that it leads to hurting myself, it went away."

msgctxt "mn19:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘parabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchati;"
msgstr "When I reflected that it leads to hurting others, it went away."

msgctxt "mn19:3.7"
msgid ""
"‘ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchati;"
msgstr "When I reflected that it leads to hurting both, it went away."

msgctxt "mn19:3.8"
msgid ""
"‘paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko anibbānasaṃvattaniko’tipi me, bhikkhave, "
"paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"When I reflected that it blocks wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it "
"doesn’t lead to extinguishment, it went away."

#. VAR: pajahameva → pajjahameva (s1-3) | pajahāmeva (pts1)
#. VAR: byantameva → byanteva (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: vinodameva → vinodanameva (s1-3) | vinodemeva (pts1)
msgctxt "mn19:3.9"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, uppannuppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ pajahameva vinodameva "
"byantameva naṃ akāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"So I gave up, got rid of, and eliminated any sensual thoughts that arose."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4-5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:4-5.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato "
"uppajjati byāpādavitakko … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a malicious thought arose …"

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.2"
msgid "uppajjati vihiṃsāvitakko."
msgstr "a cruel thought arose."

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāmi:"
msgstr "I understood:"

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.4"
msgid "‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ vihiṃsāvitakko."
msgstr "‘This cruel thought has arisen in me."

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.5"
msgid ""
"So ca kho attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, "
"ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko "
"anibbānasaṃvattaniko’."
msgstr ""
"It leads to hurting myself, hurting others, and hurting both. It blocks "
"wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it doesn’t lead to extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.6"
msgid ""
"‘Attabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchati;"
msgstr "When I reflected that it leads to hurting myself …"

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.7"
msgid ""
"‘parabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchati;"
msgstr "hurting others …"

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.8"
msgid ""
"‘ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattatī’tipi me, bhikkhave, paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchati;"
msgstr "hurting both, it went away."

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.9"
msgid ""
"‘paññānirodhiko vighātapakkhiko anibbānasaṃvattaniko’tipi me, bhikkhave, "
"paṭisañcikkhato abbhatthaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"When I reflected that it blocks wisdom, it’s on the side of anguish, and it "
"doesn’t lead to extinguishment, it went away."

msgctxt "mn19:4-5.10"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, uppannuppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ pajahameva vinodameva "
"byantameva naṃ akāsiṃ."
msgstr "So I gave up, got rid of, and eliminated any cruel thoughts that arose."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:6.1"
msgid ""
"Yaññadeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, tathā tathā "
"nati hoti cetaso."
msgstr ""
"Whatever a mendicant frequently thinks about and considers becomes their "
"heart’s inclination."

msgctxt "mn19:6.2"
msgid ""
"Kāmavitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, pahāsi "
"nekkhammavitakkaṃ, kāmavitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassa taṃ kāmavitakkāya cittaṃ "
"namati."
msgstr ""
"If they often think about and consider sensual thoughts, they’ve given up "
"the thought of renunciation to cultivate sensual thought. Their mind "
"inclines to sensual thoughts."

msgctxt "mn19:6.3"
msgid "Byāpādavitakkañce, bhikkhave … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If they often think about and consider malicious thoughts … their mind "
"inclines to malicious thoughts."

msgctxt "mn19:6.4"
msgid ""
"vihiṃsāvitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, "
"pahāsi avihiṃsāvitakkaṃ, vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassa taṃ "
"vihiṃsāvitakkāya cittaṃ namati."
msgstr ""
"If they often think about and consider cruel thoughts … their mind inclines "
"to cruel thoughts."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye kiṭṭhasambādhe "
"gopālako gāvo rakkheyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose it’s the last month of the rainy season, when the crops grow closely "
"together, and a cowherd must take care of the cattle."

msgctxt "mn19:7.2"
msgid ""
"So tā gāvo tato tato daṇḍena ākoṭeyya paṭikoṭeyya sannirundheyya "
"sannivāreyya."
msgstr ""
"He’d tap and poke them with his staff on this side and that to keep them in "
"check."

msgctxt "mn19:7.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn19:7.4"
msgid ""
"Passati hi so, bhikkhave, gopālako tatonidānaṃ vadhaṃ vā bandhanaṃ vā jāniṃ "
"vā garahaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"For he sees that if they wander into the crops he could be executed, "
"imprisoned, fined, or condemned."

msgctxt "mn19:7.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, addasaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ "
"saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, I saw that unskillful qualities have drawbacks, depravity, "
"and corruption, and that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing "
"power of renunciation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.116"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:8.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato "
"uppajjati nekkhammavitakko."
msgstr ""
"Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a thought of renunciation "
"arose."

msgctxt "mn19:8.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāmi:"
msgstr "I understood:"

msgctxt "mn19:8.3"
msgid "‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ nekkhammavitakko."
msgstr "‘This thought of renunciation has arisen in me."

msgctxt "mn19:8.4"
msgid ""
"So ca kho nevattabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na "
"ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattati, paññāvuddhiko avighātapakkhiko "
"nibbānasaṃvattaniko’."
msgstr ""
"It doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both. It "
"nourishes wisdom, it’s on the side of freedom from anguish, and it leads to "
"extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn19:8.5"
msgid ""
"Rattiñcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ "
"bhayaṃ samanupassāmi."
msgstr "If I were to keep on thinking and considering this all night …"

msgctxt "mn19:8.6"
msgid ""
"Divasañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ "
"bhayaṃ samanupassāmi."
msgstr "all day …"

msgctxt "mn19:8.7"
msgid ""
"Rattindivañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva "
"tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi."
msgstr "all night and day, I see no danger that would come from that."

msgctxt "mn19:8.8"
msgid "Api ca kho me aticiraṃ anuvitakkayato anuvicārayato kāyo kilameyya."
msgstr "Still, thinking and considering for too long would tire my body."

#. VAR: kilante → kilamante (mr)
msgctxt "mn19:8.9"
msgid "Kāye kilante cittaṃ ūhaññeyya."
msgstr "And when the body is tired, the mind is stressed."

msgctxt "mn19:8.10"
msgid "Ūhate citte ārā cittaṃ samādhimhāti."
msgstr "And when the mind is stressed, it’s far from immersion."

#. VAR: sannisādemi ekodiṃ karomi → ekodi karomi (pts1)
msgctxt "mn19:8.11"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, ajjhattameva cittaṃ saṇṭhapemi sannisādemi ekodiṃ "
"karomi samādahāmi."
msgstr "So I stilled, settled, unified, and immersed my mind internally."

msgctxt "mn19:8.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. VAR: ūhaññī’ti → ugghāṭīti (s1-3, mr) | ūhanīti (pts1)
msgctxt "mn19:8.13"
msgid "‘Mā me cittaṃ ūhaññī’ti."
msgstr "So that my mind would not be stressed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9-10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:9-10.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato "
"uppajjati abyāpādavitakko … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Then, as I meditated—diligent, keen, and resolute—a thought of love arose …"

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.2"
msgid "uppajjati avihiṃsāvitakko."
msgstr "a thought of kindness arose."

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāmi:"
msgstr "I understood:"

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.4"
msgid "‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ avihiṃsāvitakko."
msgstr "‘This thought of kindness has arisen in me."

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.5"
msgid ""
"So ca kho nevattabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāya saṃvattati, na "
"ubhayabyābādhāya saṃvattati, paññāvuddhiko avighātapakkhiko "
"nibbānasaṃvattaniko’."
msgstr ""
"It doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both. It "
"nourishes wisdom, it’s on the side of freedom from anguish, and it leads to "
"extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.6"
msgid ""
"Rattiñcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ "
"bhayaṃ samanupassāmi."
msgstr "If I were to keep on thinking and considering this all night …"

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.7"
msgid ""
"Divasañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva tatonidānaṃ "
"bhayaṃ samanupassāmi."
msgstr "all day …"

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.8"
msgid ""
"Rattindivañcepi naṃ, bhikkhave, anuvitakkeyyaṃ anuvicāreyyaṃ, neva "
"tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ samanupassāmi."
msgstr "all night and day, I see no danger that would come from that."

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.9"
msgid "Api ca kho me aticiraṃ anuvitakkayato anuvicārayato kāyo kilameyya."
msgstr "Still, thinking and considering for too long would tire my body."

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.10"
msgid "Kāye kilante cittaṃ ūhaññeyya."
msgstr "And when the body is tired, the mind is stressed."

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.11"
msgid "Ūhate citte ārā cittaṃ samādhimhāti."
msgstr "And when the mind is stressed, it’s far from immersion."

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.12"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, ajjhattameva cittaṃ saṇṭhapemi, sannisādemi, ekodiṃ "
"karomi samādahāmi."
msgstr "So I stilled, settled, unified, and immersed my mind internally."

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.13"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn19:9-10.14"
msgid "‘Mā me cittaṃ ūhaññī’ti."
msgstr "So that my mind would not be stressed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.117"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:11.1"
msgid ""
"Yaññadeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, tathā tathā "
"nati hoti cetaso."
msgstr ""
"Whatever a mendicant frequently thinks about and considers becomes their "
"heart’s inclination."

msgctxt "mn19:11.2"
msgid ""
"Nekkhammavitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, "
"pahāsi kāmavitakkaṃ, nekkhammavitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassaṃ taṃ "
"nekkhammavitakkāya cittaṃ namati."
msgstr ""
"If they often think about and consider thoughts of renunciation, they’ve "
"given up sensual thought to cultivate the thought of renunciation. Their "
"mind inclines to thoughts of renunciation."

msgctxt "mn19:11.3"
msgid "Abyāpādavitakkañce, bhikkhave … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If they often think about and consider thoughts of love … their mind "
"inclines to thoughts of love."

msgctxt "mn19:11.4"
msgid ""
"avihiṃsāvitakkañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bahulamanuvitakketi anuvicāreti, "
"pahāsi vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ, avihiṃsāvitakkaṃ bahulamakāsi, tassa taṃ "
"avihiṃsāvitakkāya cittaṃ namati."
msgstr ""
"If they often think about and consider thoughts of kindness … their mind "
"inclines to thoughts of kindness."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:12.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse sabbasassesu gāmantasambhatesu "
"gopālako gāvo rakkheyya, tassa rukkhamūlagatassa vā abbhokāsagatassa vā "
"satikaraṇīyameva hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Suppose it’s the last month of summer, when all the crops have been gathered "
"into the neighborhood of a village, and a cowherd must take care of the "
"cattle. While at the root of a tree or in the open he need only be mindful "
"that"

#. VAR: etā → ete (mr)
msgctxt "mn19:12.2"
msgid "‘etā gāvo’ti."
msgstr "the cattle are there."

msgctxt "mn19:12.3"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, satikaraṇīyameva ahosi:"
msgstr "In the same way I needed only to be mindful that"

msgctxt "mn19:12.4"
msgid "‘ete dhammā’ti."
msgstr "those things were there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:13.1"
msgid ""
"Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhikkhave, vīriyaṃ ahosi asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati "
"asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ."
msgstr ""
"My energy was roused up and unflagging, my mindfulness was established and "
"lucid, my body was tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind was immersed in "
"samādhi."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:14.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I "
"entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:15.1"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered "
"and remained in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born "
"of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, "
"without placing the mind and keeping it connected."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:16.1"
msgid ""
"Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihāsiṃ sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedesiṃ, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti, "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, I entered and remained in the third "
"absorption, where I meditated with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally "
"experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and "
"mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:17.1"
msgid ""
"Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"With the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness "
"and sadness, I entered and remained in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:18.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, "
"rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I "
"extended it toward recollection of past lives."

msgctxt "mn19:18.2"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi. Seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti "
"sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi."
msgstr "I recollected many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:19.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhikkhave, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā;"
msgstr ""
"This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the "
"night."

msgctxt "mn19:19.2"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:20.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had become immersed in samādhi like this, I extended it toward "
"knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn19:20.2"
msgid ""
"So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne … pe … ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā … pe … "
"iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate, yathākammūpage "
"satte pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings "
"passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in "
"a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn "
"according to their deeds."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:21.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhikkhave, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā vijjā adhigatā;"
msgstr ""
"This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the "
"night."

msgctxt "mn19:21.2"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:22.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had become immersed in samādhi like this, I extended it toward "
"knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn19:22.2"
msgid ""
"So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘"
"ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ …"
" ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to "
"the cessation of suffering.'"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:23.1"
msgid ""
"‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ "
"āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of defilements.'"

msgctxt "mn19:23.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti "
"ñāṇaṃ ahosi:"
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "mn19:23.3"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:24.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhikkhave, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā vijjā adhigatā;"
msgstr ""
"This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the "
"night."

msgctxt "mn19:24.2"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:25.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, araññe pavane mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that in a forested wilderness there was an expanse of low-lying "
"swampland,"

msgctxt "mn19:25.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ mahāmigasaṅgho upanissāya vihareyya."
msgstr "and a large herd of deer lived nearby."

msgctxt "mn19:25.3"
msgid "Tassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya anatthakāmo ahitakāmo ayogakkhemakāmo."
msgstr "Then along comes a person who wants to harm, injure, and threaten them."

msgctxt "mn19:25.4"
msgid ""
"So yvāssa maggo khemo sovatthiko pītigamanīyo taṃ maggaṃ pidaheyya, "
"vivareyya kummaggaṃ, odaheyya okacaraṃ, ṭhapeyya okacārikaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They close off the safe, secure path that leads to happiness, and open the "
"wrong path. There they plant domesticated male and female deer as decoys"

#. VAR: anayabyasanaṃ → anayabyasanaṃ tanuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn19:25.5"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, mahāmigasaṅgho aparena samayena anayabyasanaṃ "
"āpajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"so that, in due course, that herd of deer would come to ruin and disaster."

msgctxt "mn19:25.6"
msgid ""
"Tasseva kho pana, bhikkhave, mahato migasaṅghassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya "
"atthakāmo hitakāmo yogakkhemakāmo."
msgstr "Then along comes a person who wants to help keep the herd of deer safe."

msgctxt "mn19:25.7"
msgid ""
"So yvāssa maggo khemo sovatthiko pītigamanīyo taṃ maggaṃ vivareyya, "
"pidaheyya kummaggaṃ, ūhaneyya okacaraṃ, nāseyya okacārikaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They open up the safe, secure path that leads to happiness, and close off "
"the wrong path. They get rid of the decoys"

msgctxt "mn19:25.8"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, mahāmigasaṅgho aparena samayena vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ "
"vepullaṃ āpajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"so that, in due course, that herd of deer would grow, increase, and mature."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.118"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:26.1"
msgid "Upamā kho me ayaṃ, bhikkhave, katā atthassa viññāpanāya."
msgstr "I’ve made up this simile to make a point."

msgctxt "mn19:26.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ cevettha attho—"
msgstr "And this is what it means."

msgctxt "mn19:26.3"
msgid "mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalanti kho, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘An expanse of low-lying swampland’ is a term for sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "mn19:26.4"
msgid "Mahāmigasaṅghoti kho, bhikkhave, sattānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘A large herd of deer’ is a term for sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn19:26.5"
msgid ""
"Puriso anatthakāmo ahitakāmo ayogakkhemakāmoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ "
"pāpimato adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘A person who wants to harm, injure, and threaten them’ is a term for Māra "
"the Wicked."

msgctxt "mn19:26.6"
msgid ""
"Kummaggoti kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhaṅgikassetaṃ micchāmaggassa adhivacanaṃ, "
"seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘The wrong path’ is a term for the wrong eightfold path, that is,"

msgctxt "mn19:26.7"
msgid ""
"micchādiṭṭhiyā micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācāya micchākammantassa "
"micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmassa micchāsatiyā micchāsamādhissa."
msgstr ""
"wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, "
"wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion."

msgctxt "mn19:26.8"
msgid "Okacaroti kho, bhikkhave, nandīrāgassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘A domesticated male deer’ is a term for desire with relishing."

msgctxt "mn19:26.9"
msgid "Okacārikāti kho, bhikkhave, avijjāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘A domesticated female deer’ is a term for ignorance."

msgctxt "mn19:26.10"
msgid ""
"Puriso atthakāmo hitakāmo yogakkhemakāmoti kho, bhikkhave, tathāgatassetaṃ "
"adhivacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"‘A person who wants to help keep the herd of deer safe’ is a term for the "
"Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "mn19:26.11"
msgid ""
"Khemo maggo sovatthiko pītigamanīyoti kho, bhikkhave, ariyassetaṃ "
"aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘The safe, secure path that leads to happiness’ is a term for the noble "
"eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn19:26.12"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhiyā sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācāya sammākammantassa sammāājīvassa "
"sammāvāyāmassa sammāsatiyā sammāsamādhissa."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:26.13"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, bhikkhave, vivaṭo mayā khemo maggo sovatthiko pītigamanīyo, pihito "
"kummaggo, ūhato okacaro, nāsitā okacārikā."
msgstr ""
"So, mendicants, I have opened up the safe, secure path to happiness and "
"closed off the wrong path. And I have got rid of the male and female decoys."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:27.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ "
"upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā."
msgstr ""
"Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best "
"for their disciples."

msgctxt "mn19:27.2"
msgid ""
"Etāni, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni; jhāyatha, bhikkhave, mā "
"pamādattha; mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice "
"absorption, mendicants! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is "
"my instruction to you.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn19:27.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn19:27.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn19:27.5"
msgid "Dvedhāvitakkasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
